data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Defining the Objective**\n\nOkay, I've started by defining the core objective: explaining quantum computing to a five-year-old. Next, I identified crucial constraints, mainly the child's short attention span. I'm focusing on simplicity and clarity. I'll need to figure out what key quantum concepts are even accessible at that age.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"totalTokenCount": 202,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 67,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Refining the Approach**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on an effective analogy for superposition, considering the \"coin spinning\" idea, as it best represents being in multiple states simultaneously. I also need to make sure this explanation is grounded in relatable concepts that a young child understands. The challenge lies in making quantum phenomena concrete and fun for them.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"totalTokenCount": 503,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 368,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Developing the Framework**\n\nI've gone back to the core concepts, aiming for a child-friendly breakdown. I've re-reviewed the concepts of superposition and entanglement, now with an eye toward concrete analogies. For superposition, I have selected a \"magic toy\" that can be red *and* blue at the same time. I need to make it cool and relatable. For entanglement, I'm thinking of best friends holding hands.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"totalTokenCount": 575,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 440,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "Okay, imagine your regular computer is like a helpful friend who can only look at one picture at a time to solve a puzzle.\n\n"}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"candidatesTokenCount": 23,"totalTokenCount": 598,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 440,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "A quantum computer is like a *magic* helpful friend! Instead of one picture, this friend can look at *all the pictures* for the puzzle *at the very same time*! And sometimes, these magic friends can even hold hands and"}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"candidatesTokenCount": 72,"totalTokenCount": 647,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 440,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": " work together super fast.\n\nThis helps them solve really, really tricky puzzles that your regular friend would take forever to figure out! It's a special kind of fast thinking!"}],"role": "model"},"finishReason": "STOP","index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 135,"candidatesTokenCount": 108,"totalTokenCount": 683,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 135}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 440,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "p-z_acTiLYng_uMPuNbMgQc"}

